              "      const buttonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#df-4286873e-80dd-4962-8795-8239bfc81059 button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "      buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-4286873e-80dd-4962-8795-8239bfc81059');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

              "\n",
              "    <script>\n",
              "      const buttonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#df-0622f1c2-9882-4218-9801-8cadd5a8c541 button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "      buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-0622f1c2-9882-4218-9801-8cadd5a8c541');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "\n",
              "\n",
              "    <div id=\"df-7949d4a9-0dc8-4b28-b596-b4e271ba1f29\">\n",

              "                style=\"display:none;\">\n",

        "# Set seaborn style\n",
        "sns.set_palette(\"muted\", color_codes=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Loop through numeric columns\n",
        "for col in numerical_cols.columns:\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Plot histogram with KDE\n",
        "    sns.histplot(data=numerical_cols, x=col, kde=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Compute descriptive stats\n",
        "    col_min = numerical_cols[col].min()\n",
        "    col_max = numerical_cols[col].max()\n",
        "    col_mean = numerical_cols[col].mean()\n",
        "    col_median = numerical_cols[col].median()\n",
        "    col_mode = numerical_cols[col].mode().iloc[0]\n",
        "    col_skewness = numerical_cols[col].skew()\n",
        "    col_std = numerical_cols[col].std()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Labels and title\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(col)\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Count\")\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"Univariate Analysis of {col}\\n\"\n",
        "              f\"min={col_min:.2f}, max={col_max:.2f}, \"\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "dependent_var = 'STUDENT_PERFORMANCE_RATING'\n",
        "\n",
        "# Cross-tabulations and Chi-square test\n",
        "crosstab_list = []\n",
        "chi2_data = []\n",
        "boxplot_vars = []\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in numerical_cols.columns:\n",
        "    if col != dependent_var:\n",
        "        ctab = pd.crosstab(numerical_cols[col], numerical_cols[dependent_var])\n",
        "        crosstab_list.append((col, ctab))\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Chi-square test\n",
        "        chi2_stat, p_val, dof, _ = chi2_contingency(ctab)\n",
        "        chi2_data.append({\n",
        "            \"Variable\": col,\n",
        "            \"Chi-Square\": chi2_stat,\n",
        "            \"p-value\": p_val,\n",
        "            \"Degrees of Freedom\": dof\n",
        "        })\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Boxplot list\n",
        "        boxplot_vars.append(col)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert chi-square results to DataFrame\n",
        "chi2_df_full = pd.DataFrame(chi2_data).sort_values(\"p-value\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display chi-square results using pandas' display function instead of ace_tools\n",
        "# This provides a default way to display the DataFrame\n",
        "display(chi2_df_full)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate boxplots\n",
        "for var in boxplot_vars:\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "    sns.boxplot(x=numerical_cols[dependent_var], y=numerical_cols[var], palette='pastel')\n",
        "    plt.title(f'Boxplot of {var} by {dependent_var}')\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(dependent_var)\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(var)\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 1000
        },
        "id": "bNMSNdi5bo4o",
        "outputId": "9d859302-c6d4-49b0-a0d9-27403d163ed9"
      },

              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-92c5c096-dd92-40b2-b81c-fa6d068595b7');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "\n",
              "\n",

              "          } catch (error) {\n",
              "            console.error('Error during call to suggestCharts:', error);\n",
              "          }\n",
              "          quickchartButtonEl.classList.remove('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "          quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",

        "# Identify columns with zero variance (same value in all rows) — not useful for modeling\n",
        "zero_var_cols = [col for col in data.columns if data[col].nunique() <= 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Zero variance columns:\", zero_var_cols)"
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Detect outliers using IQR and manual bounds on Likert scale (e.g scale: 1 to 5)\n",
        "outlier_summary = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in numerical_cols.columns:\n",
        "   # IQR Method\n",
        "    Q1 = numerical_cols[col].quantile(0.25)\n",
        "    Q3 = numerical_cols[col].quantile(0.75)\n",
        "    IQR = Q3 - Q1\n",
        "    iqr_outliers = numerical_cols[(numerical_cols[col] < Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) | (numerical_cols[col] > Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Manual bound check (for Likert-type scales assumed from 1 to 5)\n",
        "    manual_outliers = numerical_cols[(numerical_cols[col] < 1) | (numerical_cols[col] > 5)]\n",
        "\n",
        "    outlier_summary[col] = {\n",
        "        \"IQR Outlier Count\": len(iqr_outliers),\n",
        "        \"Manual Bound Violation Count\": len(manual_outliers)\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert summary to DataFrame\n",
        "outlier_summary_data = pd.DataFrame(outlier_summary).T\n",
        "print(outlier_summary_data)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "Faw2LK9yraXc",
        "outputId": "9ac7d801-6f56-4005-b26f-0b7c77aadad4"
      },
      "execution_count": 103,
      "outputs": [

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Define the columns with outliers\n",
        "outlier_cols = ['GENERAL_APPEARANCE', 'GENERAL_POINT_AVERAGE']\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in outlier_cols:\n",
        "    Q1 = data[col].quantile(0.25)\n",
        "    Q3 = data[col].quantile(0.75)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Compute the Interquartile Range (IQR)\n",
        "    IQR = Q3 - Q1\n",
        "    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR\n",
        "    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Cap the values outside the bounds\n",
        "    data[col] = data[col].clip(lower=lower_bound, upper=upper_bound)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Identify any remaining outliers (should be none after capping)\n",
        "    outliers = data[(data[col] < lower_bound) | (data[col] > upper_bound)]\n",
        "    print(f\"{col} - Remaining IQR Outliers: {len(outliers)}\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Get the piechart vaariables\n",
        "def pie_chart_var(col_name, data):\n",
        "    counts = [g.shape[0] for _,g in  data.groupby(col_name)]\n",
        "    headers = [g.loc[:,col_name].iloc[0] for _,g in  data.groupby(col_name)]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get percentages\n",
        "    percentages = np.array(counts) / np.array(counts).sum() *100\n",
        "    headers = [f\"{label} - {round(percentage,2)}%\" for label, percentage in zip(headers, percentages)]\n",
        "\n",
        "    return counts, headers\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the figure\n",
        "col = 3\n",
        "row = math.ceil(len(data.columns)/col)\n",
        "fig,ax = plt.subplots(row,col, figsize=(20,10), layout='constrained')\n",
        "\n",
        "for idx, ax in enumerate(ax.flatten()):\n",
        "    if idx < len(data.columns):\n",
        "        col_name = list(data.columns)[idx]\n",
        "        counts, headers = pie_chart_var(col_name, data)\n",
        "        ax.pie(counts, labels=headers)\n",
        "        ax.set_title(f\"Population {col_name.title()}\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        ax.remove()\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.suptitle(\"Population Pie Chart by Features\", fontsize=20)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

      "source": [
        "# Split features and target\n",
        "X = data.drop(['CLASS'], axis=1)\n",
        "y = data['CLASS']"

    {
      "source": [
        "# Define models and hyperparameter distributions\n",
        "model_defs = {\n",
        "     'SVM': (SVC(probability=True, random_state=42), {\n",
        "        'C': [0.1, 1, 10],\n",
        "        'gamma': [0.1, 1, 10],\n",
        "        'kernel': ['rbf']\n",
        "    }),\n",
        "    'Decision Tree': (DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42), {\n",
        "        'max_depth': [5, 10, 15],\n",
        "        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]\n",
        "    }),\n",
        "    'Logistic Regression': (LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42), {\n",
        "        'C': [0.1, 1, 10],\n",
        "        'penalty': ['l2']\n",
        "    }),\n",
        "    'KNN': (KNeighborsClassifier(), {\n",
        "        'n_neighbors': [3, 5, 7],\n",
        "        'weights': ['uniform', 'distance']\n",
        "    })\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "results = {}\n",
        "best_model = None\n",
        "best_f1 = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train models with RandomizedSearchCV\n",
        "for name, (model, param_dist) in model_defs.items():\n",
        "    print(f\"Training {name}...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    search = RandomizedSearchCV(\n",
        "        estimator=model,\n",
        "        param_distributions=param_dist,\n",
        "        n_iter=10,  # Try 10 random combinations\n",
        "        scoring='f1',\n",
        "        cv=5,\n",
        "        n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "        random_state=42\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    search.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "    best_est = search.best_estimator_\n",
        "    y_pred = best_est.predict(X_test)\n",
        "    y_prob = best_est.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "    results[name] = {\n",
        "        'accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),\n",
        "        'precision': precision_score(y_test, y_pred),\n",
        "        'recall': recall_score(y_test, y_pred),\n",
        "        'f1': f1_score(y_test, y_pred),\n",
        "        'roc_auc': roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob),\n",
        "        'confusion_matrix': confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred),\n",
        "        'best_params': search.best_params_\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    if results[name]['f1'] > best_f1:\n",
        "        best_f1 = results[name]['f1']\n",
        "        best_model = best_est\n",
        "\n",
        "# Save the best model\n",
        "joblib.dump(best_model, 'employability_predictor.pkl')\n"
      ],
      "cell_type": "code",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Plot Learning Curve for SVM (Best model)\n",
        "def plot_learning_curve(estimator, title, X, y):\n",
        "    train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(\n",
        "        estimator, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy', n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "        train_sizes=np.linspace(.1, 1.0, 5), random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)\n",
        "    test_scores_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure()\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Training examples\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Accuracy\")\n",
        "    plt.grid()\n",
        "    plt.plot(train_sizes, train_scores_mean, 'o-', color=\"r\", label=\"Training score\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(train_sizes, test_scores_mean, 'o-', color=\"g\", label=\"Cross-validation score\")\n",
        "    plt.legend(loc=\"best\")\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Use the best SVM model found during the random search for the learning curve\n",
        "# Access the best parameters for SVM from the 'results' dictionary and create a new SVC instance\n",
        "best_svm_params = results[\"SVM\"][\"best_params\"]\n",
        "best_svm_model = SVC(probability=True, random_state=42, **best_svm_params)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Use y_train_res which was the variable name used in the SMOTE step\n",
        "plot_learning_curve(best_svm_model, \"Learning Curve: SVM\", X_train, y_train)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

        "param_range = [0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100]\n",
        "train_scores, test_scores = validation_curve(\n",
        "    SVC(kernel='rbf', gamma=5), X_train, y_train,\n",
        "    param_name='C', param_range=param_range,\n",
        "    cv=5, scoring='f1', n_jobs=-1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)\n",

        "# Plot\n",
        "plt.figure()\n",
        "plt.semilogx(param_range, train_scores_mean, label=\"Training F1 Score\", marker='o')\n",

              "<IPython.core.display.Javascript object>"
            ],
            "application/javascript": [
              "\n",
              "    async function download(id, filename, size) {\n",
              "      if (!google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed) {\n",
              "        return;\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      const div = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "      const label = document.createElement('label');\n",
              "      label.textContent = `Downloading \"${filename}\": `;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(label);\n",
              "      const progress = document.createElement('progress');\n",
              "      progress.max = size;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(progress);\n",
              "      document.body.appendChild(div);\n",
              "\n",
              "      const buffers = [];\n",
              "      let downloaded = 0;\n",
              "\n",
              "      const channel = await google.colab.kernel.comms.open(id);\n",
              "      // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n",
              "      channel.send({})\n",
              "\n",
              "      for await (const message of channel.messages) {\n",
              "        // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n",
              "        channel.send({})\n",
              "        if (message.buffers) {\n",
              "          for (const buffer of message.buffers) {\n",
              "            buffers.push(buffer);\n",
              "            downloaded += buffer.byteLength;\n",
              "            progress.value = downloaded;\n",
              "          }\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      const blob = new Blob(buffers, {type: 'application/binary'});\n",
              "      const a = document.createElement('a');\n",
              "      a.href = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n",
              "      a.download = filename;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(a);\n",
              "      a.click();\n",
              "      div.remove();\n",
              "    }\n",
              "  "
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {}
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<IPython.core.display.Javascript object>"

              "        return;\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      const div = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "      const label = document.createElement('label');\n",
              "      label.textContent = `Downloading \"${filename}\": `;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(label);\n",

              "      progress.max = size;\n",
              "      div.appendChild(progress);\n",
              "      document.body.appendChild(div);\n",
              "\n",
              "      const buffers = [];\n",
              "      let downloaded = 0;\n",
              "\n",
              "      const channel = await google.colab.kernel.comms.open(id);\n",
              "      // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n",
              "      channel.send({})\n",
              "\n",
              "      for await (const message of channel.messages) {\n",
              "        // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n",
              "        channel.send({})\n",
              "        if (message.buffers) {\n",
              "          for (const buffer of message.buffers) {\n",
              "            buffers.push(buffer);\n",
              "            downloaded += buffer.byteLength;\n",
              "            progress.value = downloaded;\n",
              "          }\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      const blob = new Blob(buffers, {type: 'application/binary'});\n",
              "      const a = document.createElement('a');\n",
              "      a.href = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n",
              "      a.download = filename;\n",

              "    }\n",
